Introduction

Purpose
This document defines the complete requirements for the Parent Child Application Form, where parents enter full details about their child and upload supporting documents. The system stores all application information in a JSON file instead of a database. The system must be developed using html and php.

Scope
The system must allow the parents to:
Enter child and parent details.
Upload required supporting documents.
Submit an application.
The system will not use database to store files but will use JSON for storage.

Functional Requirements
1.1 Child Information required fields:
Child Full Name
Date of Birth
Gender
Grade Applying For
Residential Address

Grade Categories
Parents must select from the following options:
Category	Age Range
Infants	        6 – 12 months
Toddlers	1 – 3 years
Playgroup	3 – 4 years
Pre-School	4 – 5 years

Selection Method
The field must be a dropdown menu or radio buttons.
The system must validate that the child’s age matches the selected category.

Default Behavior
Dropdown should display “Select Category” by default.
Other categories should be disabled if the age does not match.

1.2 Parent Information required fields:
Parent Full Name
Relationship to Child
Email Address
Phone Number
Residential Address

Validation:
Email must be a valid format.
Phone number must match a valid number pattern.

1.3 Supporting Documents Upload:
Parents must upload the following:
Birth Certificate
Parent/Guardian ID

Validation:
Allowed formats: PDF, JPG, PNG
Max size: 2MB per file
Multiple upload attempts allowed
System must show a preview if document is an image
System must reject invalid file types
System must show error messages for failed uploads

1.4 Submission Requirements:
Upon submitting the form:
All fields must be validated.
All documents must be uploaded.
Application will only save if validation passes.
Application status defaults to "pending".
A success message must be displayed after submission and parent must view summary of submission.

1.5 JSON File Handling
New applications must not overwrite existing applications.
New object must be appended per application.
JSON file must remain well-structured and readable.

1.6 Validation Requirements
All required fields must be completed
Email must include “@” and valid domain
Phone number must be numeric and properly formatted
Date of birth cannot be a future date
Grade must be selected
Check file type before upload
Check file size before upload
Show real-time error messages

Page Layout of the admission page

================================================================================
                        SCHOOL ADMISSION FORM
================================================================================

SECTION 1: CHILD DETAILS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[Child Full Name:        ____________________________]  *Required
[Date of Birth:          ____/____/________]          *Required
[Gender:                 ( ) Male   ( ) Female   ( ) Other]  *Required
[Grade Applying For:     ⬇ Select Category *]        *Required
   - Infants (6-12 months)
   - Toddlers (1-3 years)
   - Playgroup (3-4 years)
   - Pre-School (4-5 years)
[Home Address:           ____________________________]  *Required
[Previous School:        ____________________________]  (Optional)

* Notes:
- Grade category must match DOB.
- If mismatch occurs, show error: "Selected category does not match child’s age."

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 2: PARENT / GUARDIAN DETAILS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[Parent Full Name:       ____________________________]  *Required
[Relationship to Child: ____________________________]  *Required
[Email Address:          ____________________________]  *Required, must be valid email
[Phone Number:           ____________________________]  *Required, numeric
[Home Address:           ____________________________]  *Required

* Notes:
- All required fields marked with "*".
- Email and phone must be validated before submission.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 3: UPLOAD SUPPORTING DOCUMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[Child ID / Birth Certificate:         [Choose File]]  *Required
[Parent ID:                           [Choose File]]  *Required
[Proof of Residence:                   [Choose File]]  *Required
[Proof of Registration / Application: [Choose File]]  *Required

* Notes:
- Allowed file types: PDF, JPG, PNG
- Max size: 2MB per file
- Preview image files if possible
- Validation error shown for invalid files

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 4: FORM VALIDATION AND SUBMISSION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[Validation Errors Display Area:      __________________]
* Real-time error messages for missing fields or invalid files

[Submit Button:                        [SUBMIT APPLICATION]]

* Notes:
- Submit button disabled until all validations pass
- After submission:
    - Save data in JSON format
    - Assign unique Application ID
    - Status defaults to "Pending"
    - Show confirmation message with Application ID and summary
